    <!-- Level 1 -->

    <element name="Choose Dragon Type" type="Class Feature" source="Worlds Collide" id="ID_WC_CLASS_FEATURE_DRAGON_TAMER_CHOOSE_DRAGON_TYPE">
        <description>
            <p>At 1st level, you choose your dragon's type between a red dragon(fire), a blue dragon(lightning),or a white dragon(ice). This dragon will then grow with you as you gain levels.</p>
        </description>
        <sheet display="false"/>
        <rules>
            <select type="Archetype" name="Dragon Type" supports="Dragon Type" level="1"/>
        </rules>
    </element>
   <element name="Summon Dragon" type="Class Feature" source="Worlds Collide" id="ID_WC_CLASS_FEATURE_DRAGON_TAMER_SUMMON_DRAGON">
        <description>
            <p>Also at 1st level, you summon a dragon to be alongside you. This dragon is a companion that gains levels with you and can be commanded to attack enemies or defend you.</p>
        </description>
        <sheet usage="1/Short Rest or -5HP">
            <description>
                <p>As a bonus action, you can summon your dragon companion up to 15ft from you. This is free once per short rest for full HP (any time) or -5 of your HP and brings dragon at Your Level*5 for health (out of combat only).</p>
            </description>
        </sheet>
    </element>

    <!-- Level 2 -->

    <element name="Dragon Anger" type="Class Feature" source="Worlds Collide" id="ID_WC_CLASS_FEATURE_DRAGON_TAMER_DRAGON_ANGER">
        <description>
            <p>At 2nd level, you and your dragon share a fierce bond. When the character or dragon drops to 0 hit points, the one still up will have advantage on attacks against the creature that brought the character down to zero, and any attack against the alive character is at disadvantage. If the character or dragon attacks a creature that did not do the blow, the attack will be at disadvantage. If the character dies, the dragon will do x2 damage on all attacks and x4 on the one that dropped character to 0 HP, or the one the caused the characters death. </p>
        </description>
        <sheet>
            <description>
                <p>When the character or dragon drops to 0 hit points, the one still up will have advantage on attacks against the creature that brought the character down to zero, and any attack against the alive character is at disadvantage. If the character or dragon attacks a creature that did not do the blow, the attack will be at disadvantage. If the character dies, the dragon will do x2 damage on all attacks and x4 on the one that dropped character to 0 HP, or the one the caused the characters death.</p>
            </description>
        </sheet>
    </element>

    <!-- Level 3 -->

    <element name="Choose Elemental Fighting Style" type="Class Feature" source="Worlds Collide" id="ID_WC_CLASS_FEATURE_DRAGON_TAMER_CHOOSE_ELEMENTAL_FIGHTING_STYLE">
